com.dooapp.gaedo.extensions.migrable
Interface Migrator

public interface Migrator

A migrator is used to transfer objects from one version to one other warning in various locations in this document we use the serialVersionUID as an example of field storing version information. This is true, as it is the role of this field. But this is also false as most of our persistence services implementations won't store a static field.

Author:
ndx

getLiveVersionFieldName

String getLiveVersionFieldName()
Get name of field used in object to store version. As an example, were serialVersionUID to be persistable, this method could return serialVersionUID

Returns:
the name of an existing field

getPersistedVersionFieldName

String getPersistedVersionFieldName()
Get the name of the "column" or equivalent concept using the given storage mechanism used to store the getLiveVersionFieldName(). This method exists to allow one to easily refactor a class without having any fear of changing the live version field name BEWAREFor optimal usage, the value returned by this method (the name of your DB column/GAE element/and so on) should NEVER change, elsewhere compatibility will be broken. This why we provide you a default value, that should theorically not conflict easily with your code.

Returns:
a good practice would be to return DEFAULT_PERSISTED_VERSION_FIELD_NAME

migrate

<DataContent,ContainedClass> DataContent migrate(FinderCrudService<ContainedClass,? extends Informer<ContainedClass>> service,
                                                 DataContent nonMigratedContent,
                                                 Object sourceVersion,
                                                 Object targetVersion)
Migrate data from a given finder service from initial version to final one

Type Parameters:
DataContent - type of content this service uses before creating objects
Parameters:
service - source service. This fild is given to easily allow different kind of behaviours when the same object is used in different contexts.
nonMigratedContent - content initially loaded from service before to be transformed into an object
sourceVersion - source version
targetVersion - target version
Returns:
a transformed content, suitable to be injected into an object of target version
